## 2. Create Product Brochure Vector Store
[Read more about the In-Memory Vector Store]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

Vector stores are powerful databases which serve the purpose of matching a user's questions to relevant parts of a document. By creating a vector store of our product catalog, we'll allow users to query using natural language.

To keep things simple, we'll use the **In-memory Vector Store** which comes built-in to n8n and doesn't require a separate service. For production deployments, I'd recommend replacing the in-memory vector store with either [Qdrant]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }} or [Pinecone]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
